<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[264,1323,283,710]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,483,509]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Discussion</emphasis>
. The female vaginal furca resembles somewhat that found in 
<taxonomicName box="[1183,1315,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1183,1315,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">G. borealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[264,358,524,550]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, except that the struts on the lower half are more heavily chitinized and are not as conspicuously twisted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
